Tactics
The Wall: The Skeleton Warriors will not charge. They will hold their position as a single unit, using their Shield Wall ability to form an almost impenetrable defensive line in front of the necromancer. Their sole purpose is to intercept melee attackers and protect their master. They will only move to engage characters who try to flank or bypass them.
The Cannon: The Apprentice Necromancer will stay behind his skeletal wall at all costs. He will open with Grave Chill on the most heavily armored party member to slow them down, then use Life Drain on subsequent turns to wear down targets and keep himself healed. If the party breaks through the skeleton line, he will use his one cast of Raise Dead in a panic to try and rebuild his wall.
Loot & Clues
Amulet of Warding: Worn by the Apprentice Necromancer. This simple silver amulet is set with a cloudy piece of amber and hums with protective magic, granting the wearer +1 DR against spells.
Necromancer's Journal: Clutched in the necromancer's hand. The last entry, written in a shaky, terrified script, reads:
"The Master's ambition is terrifying. He calls it 'apotheosis,' but it looks like madness to me. He truly thinks he can become a god of bone... a colossus. The Altmer and Dunmer humor him, but I hear them whispering when they think I'm not listening. They speak of the 'funnel,' and how the backlash from Lucien's inevitable failure will be all the power they need for their true purpose. I don't care who wins. I just want to survive this."
Scattered Treasure: A successful Standard Guile roll to search the disturbed grave goods will yield 200 gold in ancient coins and 2 Potions of Healing.

Chamber 2: The Ritual Chamber
Read Aloud:
"You descend a short flight of stone stairs into a larger, circular chamber. The room is dominated by a massive, blood-stained stone altar carved with spiraling necromantic circles. Six stone sarcophagi, their heavy lids pushed aside, ring the room.
The source of the blood is horrifyingly clear. Three of the missing mercenaries hang from rusted iron chains above the altar. They are still alive, groaning in unconscious agony as their blood drips down into grooves in the stone, feeding the glowing runes.
Two robed figures—an elegant Altmer woman and a scarred Dunmer man—stand at separate stone lecterns, their hands raised as they chant in a discordant unison. The very air crackles with building power. You have only moments before whatever dark work they are doing reaches its terrible conclusion."
The Challenge: Stop the Ritual AND Save the Mercenaries
Time Pressure: The party has 3 rounds to disrupt the ritual. At the end of the third round, the ritual completes.
Consequences of Failure: If the ritual completes, the three mercenaries die instantly and are reanimated as 3x Vengeful Wraiths (Adept Tier, TL 1 Skirmishers) who will attack the party. The two necromancers are also empowered, each immediately regaining 15 HP.
Disrupting the Ritual (Player Agency)
The ritual can be disrupted by achieving one of the following objectives:
Kill both necromancers.
Destroy both stone lecterns. (Each lectern has 15 HP and DR 3).
Free all three mercenaries. (Requires a Standard Agility roll as a Minor Action for each mercenary).
Block the Blood Flow (Creative Solution): A player can attempt to block the grooves feeding the altar. This requires a creative use of a spell (like an ice wall) or an object and a successful Standard skill roll determined by the GM.
