Tactics: The Undying Orchestra
The Conductor (Lucien): Lucien will stay at the back, using the platform and sarcophagi for cover. He is a commander. He will use Command Undead on his Bonemen to have them teleport and harass the party's backline. He will use Necrotic Bolt to apply pressure and save his more powerful spells for Phase 2.
The Minions: The Skeletons form a shield wall to protect Lucien, while the Bonemen use their teleportation to create chaos and target vulnerable party members.
Ylva's Job: "I'll handle the small fry! You get the fancy one!" Ylva will immediately engage the Skeletons, using her Cleave to deal with multiple targets and keep them from swarming the party.

PHASE 2: The Bone Colossus
Transformation Trigger: At the start of the 4th round of combat, OR when Lucien is reduced to 50% HP (whichever comes first).
Read Aloud:
"Lucien staggers back, either from your relentless assault or the sheer strain of his summoning. He spits a glob of blood and screams in fury. 'Enough! The performance is over! Now, witness the masterpiece!'
He plunges a ritual dagger into his own chest. The Soul Cairn rift behind him roars, sucking his soul from his body. But instead of dying, his form begins to change. The remaining skeletons and bonemen on the field crumble to dust, their energy pulled into their master. Lucien's body swells, bones cracking and reshaping with sickening speed. He grows to a monstrous ten feet tall, a hulking colossus of fused bone, spectral energy, and pure necromantic rage. The man is gone. In his place is a monster."
The Bone Colossus:
HP: All remaining HP from Phase 1, plus an additional 50 HP. 
DR:1 (Thick Bone Plating)
Damage: 15 (Colossal Slam, with Bone Breaker property)
New Ability - Colossal Stomp (Major Action): The Colossus slams the ground. All creatures within 20 feet must make a Hard (-2) Agility roll or be knocked prone and take 5 damage.
New Ability - Soul-Vortex Aura: A constant, 15-foot aura of draining energy. Any living creature that starts its turn within the aura takes 2 irreducible necrotic damage.
Weak Point - The Heartlight: The original necromancer's soul now burns like a green star in the creature's chest cavity. Ranged attacks targeting the Heartlight are made with a Hard (-2) penalty. A successful hit deals an extra 5 damage and temporarily disables the Soul-Vortex Aura for one round.
Tactics: The Juggernaut
The Colossus will now charge into the center of the party, using Colossal Stomp to disrupt their formation and maximizing the number of targets in its Soul-Vortex Aura. It will focus its devastating slam attacks on the character who poses the greatest threat.
Ylva's Role: "Oh, he got bigger! THIS IS THE BEST PART!" Ylva will now focus entirely on the Colossus. She will use her Tower of Strength to remain standing against its stomps and will relentlessly attack it, providing a crucial source of consistent melee damage while the party repositions and targets the weak point.

PHASE 3: The Final Desecration
Transformation Trigger: When the Bone Colossus is reduced to 25% HP or less.
Read Aloud:
"With a final, shattering blow, you crack the Colossus's bone plating. It stumbles back, green light pouring from its wounds. It lets out a roar of pure agony and desperation, and raises its massive claws to the ceiling.
'If I cannot master this tomb... THEN NONE SHALL LEAVE IT!'
The Soul Cairn rift flares violently, and the entire chamber begins to shake. Cracks spread across the ceiling as the Colossus channels all its remaining power into one final, apocalyptic spell."
The Final Spell: Cairn's Collapse
The Countdown: The GM will announce, "You have one round to stop it." At the end of the next round, the spell completes. The ceiling collapses, dealing 20 irreducible damage to everyone in the room (a near-certain TPK).
The Interruption: The spell can only be stopped by dealing 30 damage to the Bone Colossus in that single round. 14
The Final Push: This is a pure DPS race.
Ylva's Moment: Seeing the danger, Ylva will shout, "EVERYONE! HIT IT WITH EVERYTHING YOU'VE GOT! NOW!" On her turn in this final round, she will use her Hircine's Merry Dance Master's Form, becoming a whirlwind of steel to contribute a massive amount of damage in the final push.
The Party's Role: The party must use their most powerful attacks, spend their remaining FP, and coordinate their assault to meet the damage threshold and stop the spell, securing victory at the last possible second.

Victory Conditions:
The Bone Harvester is destroyed.
The party survives.
Boss Loot:
Robes of the Lich Lord: A set of master-crafted necromancer robes (DR 4) that are cold to the touch and seem to drink the light. They grant the wearer +2 max FP and, once per adventure, allow them to cast the Expert Conjuration spell Dread Zombie for 0 FP.
Skull of Binding: The necromancer's personal focus, a human skull etched with glowing green runes that pulse with a faint, sorrowful light. This profane artifact can be used to cast the Soul Trap spell three times per adventure (0 FP cost). It functions as a reusable soul gem for those three souls.
Necromancer's Grimoire: A heavy tome bound in what is unmistakably human skin, its pages filled with the necromancer's forbidden research. A character who spends a Long Rest studying it can learn the Master-tier Destruction spell Lightning Storm.
800 gold in the form of black soul gems and rare, profane ritual components.
Ancient Silver-Blood War Horn: Lying on the main altar is a beautifully carved horn made from a mammoth's tusk, inlaid with silver runes. This is the family heirloom Thongvor's ancestors were buried with.

Part V: The Aftermath
Ylva's Joyful Farewell
With the Bone Harvester destroyed and the rift to the Soul Cairn sealed, the oppressive magical energy in the cairn dissipates. The howling is gone, replaced by a profound silence. Ylva the Cleaver plants her axe into the stone floor and lets out a booming, satisfied laugh that echoes through the tomb.
Read Aloud:
"Ylva wipes a streak of bone dust and necrotic ichor from her cheek with the back of her gauntlet, her grin stretching from ear to ear. 'THAT WAS AMAZING! He got so big at the end! Did you see the way his bones cracked? Beautiful! You all fight really well! I haven't had that much fun in MONTHS!'
She claps the nearest party member on the shoulder hard enough to stagger them, a gesture of profound, bone-jarring camaraderie.
'Listen,' she says, her voice still buzzing with adrenaline, 'I'm heading back to Rorikstead—got a whole mammoth to butcher for the inn, and it's not getting any fresher. But if you ever, ever need someone for a really good fight? You know where to find me!' She winks, her eyes sparkling with predatory delight. 'Ask for the Cleaver. Everyone knows me!'
With a final, cheerful wave, she turns, activates a hidden exit, and bounds out of the tomb, humming a jaunty Nord drinking song. You hear her happy, booming voice fade into the hills, leaving you in the sudden, echoing quiet of the cleansed cairn."
Return to Markarth
The party returns to Understone Keep with their proof: the heads of the three necromancers and, more importantly, the recovered Silver-Blood War Horn.
Thongvor's Payment
Thongvor receives you in the same study. He examines the proof with a critical eye, then gives a single, sharp nod of approval when he sees the ancient war horn placed on his desk.
Read Aloud:
"Thongvor picks up the war horn, his calloused fingers tracing the silver inlays. He doesn't smile, but the hard lines around his eyes soften for a fraction of a second. 'My great-grandfather's. It was said he blew a note that could shatter a glacier.' He places it carefully on a display stand. 'You have done the Silver-Blood family a service. That's worth remembering in the Reach.'
He pushes the four heavy purses of gold across the desk, along with four smaller, but still substantial, bonus purses.
'Fourteen hundred each, as agreed. And two hundred more for the return of my family's honor. Your payment is rendered in full. Your work here is done.'"
The Survivors' Gratitude
If the mercenaries were saved in Chamber 2, word of the party's skill and heroism spreads quickly through the mercenary dens and taverns of Markarth. The party gains a positive reputation in the city as professionals who get the job done and, more importantly, look after their own.
Experience Gained: Each player gains 1 Advancement Point for completing the adventure.

GM's Quick Reference Appendix
Combat Encounter Summary (Total: 4)
Chamber 1: 1x Apprentice Necromancer & 4x Skeleton Warriors. (Tactical Challenge: Breaking a shield wall).
Chamber 2: 2x Necromancers (Controller & Artillery) & 3-round timer. (Tactical Challenge: Split objectives under time pressure).
Chamber 3: 1x Necromancer Soul-Binder & 2x Silver-Blood Ancestors. Ylva joins after Round 1. (Tactical Challenge: Dealing with teleporting skirmishers and a controlling spellcaster).
Chamber 4: 1x Master Necromancer (Lucien) with two phases & minion waves. Ylva assists. (Tactical Challenge: A multi-phase boss fight with heavy emphasis on crowd control and DPS).
Total Time Breakdown
Hook (Markarth): 10 minutes
Travel & Approach: 10 minutes
Chamber 1: 20 minutes
Chamber 2: 25 minutes
Chamber 3: 20 minutes
Chamber 4 (Boss): 30 minutes
Aftermath & Wrap-up: 10 minutes
Total Estimated Time: ~2 hours, 5 minutes (+ buffer for roleplaying and tactical discussion)
Key Pacing Notes
Combat-Focused: This is a fast-paced dungeon crawl. Keep the action moving from one chamber to the next.
Ylva as an Ally: Ylva is controlled by the GM. Her purpose is to assist, not to dominate. Use her to handle minions and support the party, allowing them to focus on the primary threats.
Time Pressure: The 3-round timer in Chamber 2 is the adventure's primary non-boss pressure point. Be clear with the players about the stakes and the countdown.
Scaling for Difficulty
If Party Struggles:
Chamber 2: Extend the ritual timer to 4 rounds.
Chamber 3: Have Ylva's entrance immediately draw the aggression of one of the Ancestors, taking pressure off the party.
Chamber 4: Reduce the HP of the Bone Colossus form by 20. Reduce the final DPS check in Phase 3 to 25 damage.
If Party Dominates:
Chamber 2: The necromancers are protected by a single Lesser Ward each (DR 3 vs. spells) that must be broken.
Chamber 3: The Soul-Binder has an additional ability: Soul Siphon (Reaction). When one of the Ancestors is destroyed, he can use his reaction to absorb its essence, healing himself for 10 HP.
Chamber 4: In Phase 2, the Bone Harvester's Soul Drain Aura also heals it for half the amount of FP it drains.
Ylva's Character Notes for GM
Personality in Combat:
Whoops and laughs when she hits or gets hit.
Enthusiastically compliments enemy attacks ("GOOD SWING!") and party members' cool moves ("NICE SHOT! DO IT AGAIN!").
Treats deadly combat like the best game in the world.
Sample Combat Dialogue:
"YOUR TURN! GET HIM!"
"OOH, THAT'S GONNA LEAVE A MARK! I LOVE IT!"
"THIS IS SO MUCH FUN!"
Not a Spotlight Stealer:
She is powerful, but her role is to make the party's victory possible, not to win the fight for them.
Her Primary Function: Crowd control and off-tanking. She handles the minions so the party can handle the bosses.
Her Goal: Make the players feel awesome. She's their biggest, loudest, and most violent cheerleader.





